02:25.687 --> 02:29.775
1x05- The Oldest Virus

02:38.075 --> 02:40.285
- This is the guy's office?
- Apparently.

02:40.285 --> 02:42.162
At the time being.

02:42.162 --> 02:43.997
Take a seat anywhere kids I'll be right with you.

02:43.997 --> 02:45.666
We're actually here to meet Harvey Thomas.

02:45.666 --> 02:47.084
Oh, um...

02:47.084 --> 02:48.293
Not here yet.

02:48.293 --> 02:51.296
- I'll point him out when he gets here.
- Thank you.

02:57.261 --> 03:01.890
I guess after Thomas' lab went bankrupt,
the creditors really came after him.

03:02.474 --> 03:05.269
- He doesn't have much left.
- Here you go.

03:05.269 --> 03:06.186
Thank you.

03:07.062 --> 03:08.897
Made him a little gunshy.

03:08.897 --> 03:10.774
You hungry?

03:21.076 --> 03:22.995
David, David!

03:22.995 --> 03:25.163
David Sandstrom. Harvey Thomas.

03:25.163 --> 03:26.081
Thomas' laboratories.

03:26.081 --> 03:28.584
I was under the impression
that you were coming alone.

03:28.584 --> 03:30.878
David is our chief scientist, Dr Thomas.

03:30.878 --> 03:32.880
He's the one got us to you.

03:32.880 --> 03:34.464
How so?

03:34.464 --> 03:38.177
Well, you've been working on a prion vaccine, right?

03:38.177 --> 03:42.890
See we detected antibodies
to Avian Leukemia Viruses in some human blood.

03:42.890 --> 03:43.974
It happens.

03:43.974 --> 03:46.685
ALV shows up in a lot of early vaccine cultures.

03:46.685 --> 03:51.190
Hey, Harv' relax. I'm not here
to take away the swimming pool, okay?

03:51.982 --> 03:53.984
All right.

03:53.984 --> 03:57.196
As I told Carol here, yes,
we were working on a prion vaccine,

03:57.196 --> 03:59.573
we had close to 30 million in the project.

03:59.573 --> 04:01.200
And then you dropped it?

04:01.200 --> 04:01.867
I had no choice.

04:01.867 --> 04:03.577
- Have you ordered breakfast?
- No thanks.

04:03.577 --> 04:04.578
We already... uh.

04:04.578 --> 04:06.788
What happened?

04:06.788 --> 04:10.167
We were close. We were very close
to coming up with the vaccine.

04:10.167 --> 04:12.586
After animal trials, we hit a brick wall.

04:12.586 --> 04:13.670
Why?

04:13.670 --> 04:16.298
We couldn't find any human volunteers.

04:16.298 --> 04:17.882
Mad cow.

04:17.882 --> 04:19.676
Scared the bejesus out of everybody.

04:19.676 --> 04:22.095
We couldn't pay people to be subjects.

04:22.095 --> 04:24.681
- There you go.
- Thanks.

04:24.681 --> 04:28.477
- Um... Are you 2 ready..
- Uh.. We're fine, actually.

04:28.477 --> 04:32.564
What happened to the recombinant prions
in the viral vectors that you created?

04:32.564 --> 04:34.566
Repossession court.

04:34.566 --> 04:38.695
Last asset I had... The only chance
I have of refinancing the lab.

04:38.695 --> 04:41.865
- Sandi, could I get.
- Can we get a sample?

04:42.491 --> 04:43.075
What for?

04:43.075 --> 04:46.078
We'd like to compare them
to some prion samples we found.

04:46.078 --> 04:50.582
Found? Where do you find prion samples?

04:50.582 --> 04:53.001
In four dead people.

05:05.389 --> 05:06.765
What's up?

05:06.765 --> 05:11.770
The kid from East LA and the most recent
victim... Both ate at Hoppen Chickens.

05:11.770 --> 05:14.565
45 franchises in California and Arizona.

05:14.565 --> 05:19.194
Sarah McKinley ate chicken tenders at Lord of the
Chicken at least 3 times in the last month.

05:19.194 --> 05:21.572
54 franchises throughout the southeast.

05:21.572 --> 05:25.075
Shasco Foods is
the wholesaler for both franchises.

05:25.075 --> 05:26.702
Well, what about the Texas veggie?

05:26.702 --> 05:29.872
Eggs. Starvest the Market.

05:29.872 --> 05:31.874
I'm on hold with the head office trying
to find out the whole sales.

05:31.874 --> 05:35.002
- Good going. 
- Thanks, I'll owe it to you.

05:35.002 --> 05:38.088
Telephony is old school Wes.

05:38.589 --> 05:41.466
Shit, did you guys change
the internet password again?

05:41.466 --> 05:41.967
Yeah.

05:41.967 --> 05:44.386
Carbon.

05:46.096 --> 05:49.183
Shasco Foods.

05:49.183 --> 05:53.270
Oh.. Number 1 egg distributor in the US.

05:53.270 --> 05:56.064
Weston, I think we have a common link.

05:57.774 --> 06:00.277
Got it Wes. Thanks.

06:00.277 --> 06:04.573
So the victims ate chicken and eggs supplied
by Wide Valley Farms.

06:04.573 --> 06:07.784
Wes set up a meeting
with their head of legal affairs.

06:07.784 --> 06:08.785
So where are we going?

06:08.785 --> 06:10.787
I'm going to see a lawyer in North Platt.

06:10.787 --> 06:12.789
You're going to a flu convention.

06:12.789 --> 06:15.167
No.. I should probably skip Chicago
and go with...

06:15.167 --> 06:20.297
David, are you gonna skip
a Spanish Flu convention to go to Nebraska?

06:20.297 --> 06:21.298
- No.
- Yeah.

06:21.298 --> 06:22.883
Thanks.

06:22.883 --> 06:24.676
What's this? We didn't order anything.

06:24.676 --> 06:25.886
Harvey did.

06:33.894 --> 06:36.688
Has there ever been a case of avian prions
found in humans?

06:36.688 --> 06:38.273
- No.
- I see.

06:38.273 --> 06:39.900
We're not talking about avian prion,

06:39.900 --> 06:42.569
we're talking about a human prion
in chickens and eggs.

06:42.569 --> 06:45.572
And you have proof that
our poultry products are contaminated?

06:45.572 --> 06:47.574
You've read our report
on where the victims ate.

06:47.574 --> 06:53.080
There are 200 million eggs and 20 million chickens
consumed every day in this country.

06:53.080 --> 06:56.083
Shasco suggested we start here, because
you're their biggest supplier.

06:56.083 --> 06:59.294
We're in price negotiations.
That's Shasco's leverage.

06:59.294 --> 07:00.796
Four people are dead.

07:00.796 --> 07:04.466
I certainly have enough to go public and
point a finger at Wide Valley Farm's chicken.

07:04.466 --> 07:08.387
- And you'd be willing to risk a lawsuit?
- You're willing to risk a PR nightmare?

07:12.891 --> 07:14.393
What is it you're asking for?

07:14.393 --> 07:17.771
We'd like you to hold all shipments
until we test your birds and eggs.

07:17.771 --> 07:20.899
You're asking us to put 50,000 people
out of work on a hunch?

07:20.899 --> 07:23.902
It's more than a hunch.

07:23.902 --> 07:26.071
You have no authority
over the food system. The FDA does.

07:26.071 --> 07:28.782
And we'll be going to the FDA
when we have proof.

07:28.782 --> 07:31.493
And we'll comply with
whatever the FDA recommends.

07:31.493 --> 07:34.496
We're asking for voluntary compliance now.

07:37.374 --> 07:39.001
We'll provide samples.

07:39.001 --> 07:42.379
But until you provide proof that
Wide Valley chicken is tainted,

07:42.880 --> 07:44.798
we keep shipping our product.

07:47.801 --> 07:49.803
Thank you.

07:56.393 --> 07:59.479
So this postdoc comes to me
with this brilliant theory on target binding,

07:59.479 --> 08:01.982
and I knew we'll screw up...
Maybe 1% chance of going anywhere,

08:01.982 --> 08:04.193
but to not try would have been crazy.

08:04.193 --> 08:06.987
And everyone was saying:
"Don't go there. Don't go there."

08:06.987 --> 08:09.072
What happened?

08:09.072 --> 08:12.284
I told her to go for it. And she listened to me.
And she was wrong.

08:12.284 --> 08:14.077
You knew she was gonna fail?

08:14.077 --> 08:16.288
There is only 99% sure.

08:16.288 --> 08:17.998
Where is she now?

08:17.998 --> 08:19.666
Med school.

08:19.666 --> 08:22.294
- Poor kid.
- David!

08:22.294 --> 08:26.298
Hey. Uh.. Thanks for
the volatile hydroxyl compounds.

08:26.298 --> 08:27.466
What the fuck are you doing here?

08:27.466 --> 08:32.095
I thought you might like a couple of tickets
to a hockey game. That..

08:32.095 --> 08:33.597
I'm playing it tonight.

08:33.597 --> 08:34.765
You made the cut.

08:34.765 --> 08:35.765
2 week charm.

08:35.765 --> 08:39.269
That's great, man. Fantastic!
You know... for an old guy.

08:39.269 --> 08:39.977
Fuck you.

08:39.977 --> 08:43.065
I'll buy you a drink.

08:43.690 --> 08:45.192
So you know that kid, Arvintchek?

08:45.192 --> 08:47.569
Yeah, with LA... Kid's a monster.
What's he like, 6'9?

08:47.569 --> 08:48.570
Uh hu.

08:48.570 --> 08:51.990
Budy checked him out. Called night. *

08:51.990 --> 08:53.992
No. I'm doing good.

08:53.992 --> 08:56.703
Good.

08:56.703 --> 08:59.581
What?

08:59.581 --> 09:02.876
I'm playing with this guy Archembault, 32.

09:02.876 --> 09:06.088
Had a heart attack.

09:06.088 --> 09:08.298
Is he okay?

09:08.298 --> 09:10.467
- Heart exploded, David.
- Jesus..

09:10.467 --> 09:12.678
What are you not telling me, Danny?

09:12.678 --> 09:14.972
I'm playing with fuckin' kids who were
in diapers when I broke in.

09:14.972 --> 09:17.266
A lot of them chewin' roids since junior high.

09:17.266 --> 09:19.685
I gotta take this shit just to fuckin'
keep the level playing field.

09:19.685 --> 09:21.895
What did you take?

09:21.895 --> 09:23.480
I don't know.

09:23.480 --> 09:24.898
Is it the same stuff as
Biriliski and Archembault?

09:27.484 --> 09:32.698
- One time, one shot. That's all it was.
- That's all it takes with synthetic hormones.

09:33.365 --> 09:39.496
David, if I can't play...
This is my life man. This is all I know.

09:39.496 --> 09:41.290
All right, give me a sample, okay?

09:41.290 --> 09:42.499
I can't.

09:42.499 --> 09:46.795
I can't. The fuckin' guy took off.
I don't know where he is.

09:48.672 --> 09:51.383
- What? Am I gonna...
- I don't know.

09:52.176 --> 09:54.386
- You got a cardiologist?
- Come on, David.

09:54.386 --> 09:58.265
Get one. Get on a treadmill,
have yourself checked out.

09:58.265 --> 09:59.474
I'm fine.

09:59.474 --> 10:04.104
So were Biriliski and Archembault, right?

10:05.397 --> 10:08.400
Order another round.
I'm gonna hit the can.

10:28.795 --> 10:30.380
- Hey.
- Gentlemen, thank you for the

10:30.380 --> 10:32.466
volatile hydroxil compounds.

10:36.803 --> 10:39.890
- Hi Hal.
- Hey, Jill. How are you?

10:39.890 --> 10:40.891
I'm well. How are you?

10:40.891 --> 10:42.267
I'm good, good.

10:42.267 --> 10:45.604
Jill Langston, MIT.
Calpinder Singh, CALTECH.

10:45.604 --> 10:46.772
- Nice to meet you.
- Hi.

10:46.772 --> 10:47.981
What are you drinkin', Jill?

10:47.981 --> 10:49.775
Club soda please.

10:49.775 --> 10:52.486
So gentlemen..

10:52.486 --> 10:55.572
I need the abstract on David Sandstrom.

10:55.572 --> 10:58.075
I've been offered
a senior position in his lab.

10:58.075 --> 10:59.701
Brilliant researcher,

11:00.285 --> 11:01.370
arrogant,

11:01.495 --> 11:04.498
and has a history of treating
his research people like shit.

11:04.498 --> 11:06.083
- Ah..
- I know.

11:06.083 --> 11:09.378
- He had to see a young postdoc once.
- You won't believe this.

11:13.298 --> 11:15.092
Yeah, I just got in. What's up?

11:15.092 --> 11:17.177
I got a district court judge
to cut through Thomas' creditors.

11:17.177 --> 11:19.304
Good. We get a sample?

11:19.304 --> 11:21.390
There weren't any to get.

11:21.390 --> 11:22.391
What are you talking about?

11:22.391 --> 11:24.685
Missing, stolen, hidden, we don't know.

11:24.685 --> 11:26.103
What did Thomas say?

11:26.103 --> 11:28.188
He didn't say anything.
We can't find him.

11:28.188 --> 11:31.275
Caroline, you realize if there are
prions in the food chain,

11:31.275 --> 11:33.068
and stored samples are missing...

11:56.675 --> 11:59.887
I'm not here.

12:05.475 --> 12:09.479
All right, I'm coming.

12:09.479 --> 12:13.483
I'm packing heat.

12:13.483 --> 12:15.694
All right, all right.

12:19.281 --> 12:20.866
What?

12:20.866 --> 12:22.701
Good morning.

12:23.285 --> 12:26.371
I'm Jill Langston. I'm here for my interview.

12:27.372 --> 12:31.168
- Caroline Morrison arranged it...
- No.. Not at 8 o'clock in the morning.

12:31.168 --> 12:34.004
That's insane. That's like 7 AM my time.

12:34.004 --> 12:35.797
No. That's 9 AM your time.

12:36.965 --> 12:38.967
- I could come back.
- No no.

12:38.967 --> 12:42.095
Come in, come in.

12:43.305 --> 12:45.974
Tell me about yourself, Jill.

12:45.974 --> 12:48.769
- You read my CV?
- Nope.

12:48.769 --> 12:49.895
Oh.

12:49.895 --> 12:56.276
Ah... Well, I did my undergrad
in molecular biology at Princeton.

12:56.276 --> 12:57.986
I'm listening.

12:57.986 --> 13:00.072
Ph.D. at Standford

13:00.072 --> 13:02.491
in virology with Colly Curie. *

13:02.491 --> 13:05.285
- My thesis was on..
- Time?

13:05.285 --> 13:06.995
I beg your pardon?

13:06.995 --> 13:09.498
On time? Was your thesis on time?

13:09.498 --> 13:11.500
Yes.

13:12.292 --> 13:15.587
Mine wasn't. It was
about 18 months late, actually.

13:15.587 --> 13:16.880
Wow, sometimes it..

13:16.880 --> 13:20.300
You can go to Stanford or Princeton
or any other fuckin' places.

13:20.300 --> 13:22.886
- Doesn't matter.
- Then why are you telling me?

13:24.304 --> 13:25.472
I'm sorry.

13:25.472 --> 13:27.683
- You asked me...
- To tell me about yourself.

13:27.683 --> 13:31.186
Your listing off institutions
like so many conquests.

13:31.186 --> 13:33.897
I'm looking for a new scientist.
Not a name dropper.

13:38.569 --> 13:41.780
I published 5 papers this year.

13:41.780 --> 13:43.991
Why don't you read them?

14:15.272 --> 14:17.691
Thomas said that his creditors
won't allow him to release the prions

14:17.691 --> 14:19.484
he made until the chapter 11 closes.

14:19.484 --> 14:22.070
Did you go to those creditors
and explained the situation?

14:22.070 --> 14:23.071
Of course.

14:23.071 --> 14:26.283
Apparently they value of their asset is
more important than the value of a human life.

14:31.705 --> 14:33.999
What is that?

14:33.999 --> 14:36.793
It looks like Wide Valley delivered their samples.

14:43.675 --> 14:45.886
So how many of these do we have coming?

14:45.886 --> 14:48.096
6 birds and a dozen eggs
from every operation.

14:48.096 --> 14:49.806
60 of operations.

14:49.806 --> 14:53.268
Okay, spines and branch with the highest
concentration of the prions we're looking for.

14:53.268 --> 14:55.270
Let's get as many people on this as possible.

14:55.270 --> 14:58.106
What if these guys turn up clean?

14:58.106 --> 14:59.983
Going to have one hell of a barbecue.

15:11.286 --> 15:12.788
Wait a minute, wait a minute,
wait a minute.

15:12.788 --> 15:15.999
Do we know how the
prions got in the chickens?

15:15.999 --> 15:19.086
No. But we have a hunch it has
something to do with Harvey Thomas.

15:19.086 --> 15:20.295
Why?

15:20.295 --> 15:24.091
He's missing, David. Along with
the prion samples he promised us.

15:24.091 --> 15:26.593
Well, I thought they were
in a repossession court lock up.

15:26.593 --> 15:28.971
Yeah, we checked. Nothing.

15:31.306 --> 15:31.974
Thank you.

15:31.974 --> 15:34.268
The FBI's been running a profile on him.

15:34.268 --> 15:37.980
He travelled to North Platt
several times in passed couple months.

15:37.980 --> 15:41.191
As in... Chicken capital of the world
North Platt?

15:41.191 --> 15:42.401
Yeah.

15:42.401 --> 15:44.570
All right. Well, thanks for the update.

15:44.570 --> 15:45.279
Sure.

15:45.279 --> 15:46.989
How is your interview with Jill Langston?

15:46.989 --> 15:48.198
Who?

15:48.198 --> 15:51.493
Jill Langston, the virologist
I wanted you to meet?

15:52.578 --> 15:54.580
Uhh...

15:54.580 --> 15:56.707
Great. Jill. Great. Went great.

15:56.707 --> 15:59.084
We'd be lucky to get her, David.

16:01.086 --> 16:04.673
Yeah well, I'm not exactly sure
she's interested in the position.

16:04.673 --> 16:06.008
You want her?

16:06.008 --> 16:07.968
Do I want her? Do I want her...

16:07.968 --> 16:10.179
- Okay, get back to me on that one.
- Okay.

16:10.179 --> 16:12.097
- Uh.. Keep me up on the chickens.
- Sure.

16:12.097 --> 16:12.890
Goodbye.

16:13.891 --> 16:17.186
The most devastating pandemic in history.

16:17.186 --> 16:22.482
We know that at least 40 million people
died between 1918 and 1919.

16:22.482 --> 16:26.278
And now it was said of the Spanish flu
that you felt a little ill at breakfast,

16:26.278 --> 16:29.907
went to bed after lunch,
and were dead by dinner.

16:29.907 --> 16:34.286
The best sample we knew would be found in
a victim burried north of the permafrost line.

16:34.286 --> 16:38.498
But our field crew failed
to find a sample with intact viral RNA.

16:38.498 --> 16:43.670
Nevertheless, I was able to sequence
the 4th of the 8 segments polymerase.

16:43.670 --> 16:45.672
The field samples were taken to..

16:45.672 --> 16:49.176
Thank you, yes. Yes. Please.

16:49.176 --> 16:51.094
Jill Langston.

16:51.094 --> 16:52.304
Dr. Sandstrom.

16:52.304 --> 16:54.389
- It's great lecture.
- Thank you.

16:54.389 --> 16:55.974
So how did you sequence polymerase?

16:55.974 --> 16:58.769
Well, that'll be in the paper I'm publishing
in Nature magazine.

16:58.769 --> 17:01.772
You got the sample from a brain.
Not a lung. Am I right?

17:01.772 --> 17:02.981
Good guess.

17:02.981 --> 17:04.398
It's how I did it.

17:04.398 --> 17:06.568
- You sequenced polymerase?
- 2 years ago.

17:06.568 --> 17:08.403
Bullshit. You didn't publish?

17:08.403 --> 17:10.696
Ah.. it's worthless unless you got the
entire genome.

17:10.696 --> 17:13.700
- Well, it's gonna be a incremental.
- Maybe.

17:13.700 --> 17:17.996
What would you say if I told you I've got a
lead on a perfect specimen?

17:18.789 --> 17:20.999
Mazeltov!

17:20.999 --> 17:24.086
Jill.. We should be
working together on this.

17:24.086 --> 17:26.296
Create a vaccine for the old lady,
you can't turn that down.

17:26.296 --> 17:27.881
Sure I can.

17:27.881 --> 17:29.800
My charms, some you'll get used to.

17:29.800 --> 17:31.593
You'll get used to my tail lights.

18:10.883 --> 18:14.803
Here is a model of the structural of the prion
from the Wide Valley chickens, on the right,

18:14.803 --> 18:17.598
and from our 4 victims, on the left.

18:17.598 --> 18:18.682
That's a match?

18:18.682 --> 18:21.185
Perfect match.

18:21.185 --> 18:23.604
So did we shutdown Wide Valley Farms?

18:23.604 --> 18:26.690
We notified the FDA at 7:15 this morning.

18:26.690 --> 18:29.109
And the bad news?

18:29.109 --> 18:31.403
In the last 6 weeks,
the Sioux City operations shipped

18:31.403 --> 18:34.990
950 thousand pounds
of chickens to Shasco,

18:34.990 --> 18:35.699
and over 2 million eggs.

18:35.699 --> 18:37.284
Where are we on Thomas?

18:37.284 --> 18:40.495
The FBI has him arriving
at Chicago at 9:15 this morning.

18:40.495 --> 18:40.996
Did they get him?

18:40.996 --> 18:41.997
Not yet.

18:41.997 --> 18:44.374
And I suppose no news
on the missing samples.

18:44.374 --> 18:47.586
